   <h2 class="subtitle"><span></span></h2>
   <h1><span>The Norwegian Government Agency for Financial Management<br /> (Senter for statlig økonomistyring)</span></h1>
 </div>
 <div class="documentBody">
   <p align="left">The Ministry of Finance has from 1 January 2004 established the Norwegian Government Agency for Financial Management. The new agency will have an important role in initiating, promoting and coordinating reforms within performance management and financial management within government. The Norwegian Government Agency for Financial Management will operate as an administrative agency with assignments within financial management formerly carried out by the Ministry of Finance, the Tax Administration and by 18 different tax inspector offices.&nbsp; </p>
<p align="left">The central unit of the agency will be an expert body for financial management. The agency will strengthen the government’s financial management by focusing on guiding and advising, standardizing, developing methods and taking other initiatives with a view towards improving performance and efficiency. The agency will for instance take care of the following concrete tasks:</p>
<ul type="disc">
<li>Give advice to the Ministry of Finance concerning establishing principles and norms for government finance management </li>
<li>Prepare advisory material, methods and tools for finance management </li>
<li>Conduct consultative functions, training and information tasks</li></ul>
<p align="left">The central unit of the agency is also responsible for tasks related to the state accounts and the governmental consolidated account system including payment transfers, and different administrative tasks. In addition, the agency will be a supplier of shared services, inter alia; personnel and payroll processing and accounting services. </p>
   <div style="clear:both">&nbsp;</div>
